odular phantom. Average geometric\ndistortion was 0.94+/-0.58 mm for the MR-Linac, 0.90+/-0.53 mm for the 1.5 T\nscanner, and 1.15+/-0.62 mm for the 3.0T scanner, for a 400 mm diameter\nvolume-of-interest. GD increased, as expected, with decreasing BW, and with the\n2D versus 3D correction algorithm. Differences in GD attributed to phantom\nset-up were 0.13 mm or less. Differences in GD for the two software\napplications were less than 0.07 mm.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 23 Mar 2020 16:12:33 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 26 Mar 2020 18:43:43 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 6 Apr 2020 18:06:35 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-10-28"}
